{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":68259,"duration_api_ms":67457,"num_turns":27,"result":"Perfect! I've completed the scout report. Here's a summary of what I found:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Milestone 3: Completeness Check + Follow-Up** requires implementing a validation and follow-up loop in the planning phase. The work is **localized to the planning subsystem** with minimal interaction with the rest of Tekhton.\n\n### Core Implementation Areas\n\n1. **`lib/plan.sh`** — Add `check_design_completeness()` function to:\n   - Detect required sections from the template\n   - Check if each section in DESIGN.md has real content (not empty, no guidance comments, no placeholders)\n   - Report incomplete sections\n\n2. **`stages/plan_interview.sh`** — Add follow-up interview loop to:\n   - Launch focused re-interview for only the incomplete sections\n   - Allow user to complete them\n   - Loop until all required sections pass\n\n3. **Prompts** — Update or create follow-up prompt variant to explain which sections need work\n\n4. **Tests** — New test coverage for completeness detection (grep/awk-based, deterministic)\n\n### Key Insight\nThe completeness check is **deterministic** — it uses grep/awk to identify empty sections, guidance comments, and placeholders. No LLM judgment needed. The follow-up loop reuses existing claude conversational mode (same as initial interview).\n\n### Complexity\n- **Files to modify**: 3-4 (lib/plan.sh, stages/plan_interview.sh, prompts, tests)\n- **Lines of change**: ~180-250\n- **Interconnected systems**: low (fully contained in planning phase)\n- **Recommended turns**: Coder 25-35, Reviewer 5-8, Tester 15-25\n\nThe SCOUT_REPORT.md has been written to `/mnt/c/Users/Geoff/workspace/geoffgodwin/tekhton/SCOUT_REPORT.md`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f9f766f5-9ca7-488e-90f6-64570ef82251","total_cost_usd":0.1091476,"usage":{"input_tokens":90,"cache_creation_input_tokens":27984,"cache_read_input_tokens":411476,"o